Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I am not sure this is a good idea.

Let's say my cloud has 2 images called "Ubuntu 14" and "Ubuntu 14.1". If I "nova boot --image "Ubuntu 14"", with this patch, it will fail because 2 images will match.

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I agree with Jordan that this could have unintended consequences.

Also it affects the v1 API. Which I don't thing should have modifications of this scale.

Patch Set 1:

So what about this change？First accurate query, if no results re fuzzy matching.Then It can be used on both sides.@Jordan Pittier,@Niall Bunting

Patch Set 1:

I am not sure this is better. This behavior will come as a surprise to many users. If the requested image doesn"t exist, we should say so loudly, not try to guess and find the best match.

I am not sure what you try to accomplish here, if a user is not sure about the name of an image, he should do a "glance image-list" first.

Patch Set 1:

I would like to make this change because of other modules to support fuzzy query such as murano.And this is friendly for users who use horizon.

Patch Set 1:

Openstack users are more in the use of horizon rather than the command line, In my opinion this change is useful.@Jordan Pittier

Patch Set 1:

Maybe what I said is not clear.I found this bug in horizon when I was searching for images.If there are hundreds of images,does not support fuzzy query will make the user feel very troublesome.My English is not good,please
bear with me.@Jordan Pittier,@Niall Bunting

Patch Set 3:

Before you get too far into this patch, this kind of query would probably be better handled by an index.  There's a new openstack project, Searchlight, that puts image metadata into elasticsearch, and it has plugins for Horizon.  You might want to look into it.  The Glance community has traditionally been against API changes that could cause too much load on the database.  I've put your patch on the agenda for the Glance drivers meeting on Tuesday, Jan 26, so we can talk about this.  https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/glance-drivers-meeting-agenda
